title: Printing Block, late 18th–early 19th century
description: Large, oblong wood block carved in relief and set with nails in allover octagonal-shaped design to form net-like ground. Pattern of naturalistic floral sprays springing from sides. At one end, four small baroque curves joining border. Block has been set in carved wood border, about two inches wide, set at right angles to the block. Pattern on this border differs at sides. Probably from other old blocks.

tombstone.epitaph: Printing Block, late 18th–early 19th century.Medium: wood, metal. 1968-45-2.
